<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Follow up with some ideas so that Slicer has a running catalog. <P>I'll start off with two:<P>Our character name and level should be denoted in the title window to allow us to figure out which window belongs to whom if we have multiple DAOC windows up.<P>Triangles on the screen should slowly fade out as they become stale over the course of a minute, this makes it easy to determine which of them are recently updated, and which are likely to be ghosts that have stealthed, gone LD, or left detection range.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Slicer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The player's name is now in the title<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sparr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Big, small, previously rejected and not, here are mine...<P>Map editing.  I dont care how, even if its just some interface to let OE pass messages to another program to create a map.<P>Spawn List exporting, preferably to something simple like a CSV (comma seperated values) list.<P>A toggle to make the map rotate instead of the character, so up is always north.<P>a list of previous locations for each spawn so you can activate a "trail" view to see where they have been, like ShowEQ.  good for finding safe spots and figuring out wander paths of important spawns<P>a local /loc display, like what the client shows.  the big numbers arent too helpful<P>Z location fading on the map, like ShowEQ.  Affecting the map and spawns, so you dont get scared by a purple 10 feet away thats actually 2 floors below you<P>more to come</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We're just getting warmed up  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I'd like to see the size of the player's white triangle increased, it's very difficult to tell what direction you are facing when zoomed out, especially if there's a white target line drawn. <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tomuchtime</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Diffrent symbols to differentiate between Mobs, player, npc's, and enemy players if possible </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lash</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Odinseye related<BR>----------------<BR>*  A toggleable radius to show you what would be visible on the game client.<P>*  Once mobs have been selected to show aggressiveness(or if this comes automatically) a visual change to mobs that will agro.  Of course there needs to be a set time when OE would forget old aggresiveness due to possible faction changes and update when you con them again.<P>*  A way to trigger a sound event when a certain mob/player is on the map.  Basically showeq spawn filtering.<P>*  An option to replay captured packets in realtime with real map updates.<P>*  A toggleable way to see gravestones on the map.  Also with an option to only show your group's gravestones and yours.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DS</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">-While looking around in RvR some PCs of opposing realms (for example britain's in hibernia) they will appear as a "green" coded mob or ally (I assume.)<P>-PC Ally characters of same realm do not con within level or color ranges on map.(at least for me they didn't.)<P>-Being able to group allies by their designated "green" shading in mob list so you can identify them more easily.<P>-Ability to update mob list by their distance and relevance to you. E.g - the closer you are to XXXX Mob, the higher he puts himself in your list.<P>Been playing too long, sorry if the wording is poor...Ugh...<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DS</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">HOLY! Completely sorry on the dual posts...mozilla wasn't updating and showing me the damn results...apologies again...<p>[This message has been edited by DS (edited 12-16-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">fodder</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would be happy if you didn't make any changes but if you give me any wishes here is what they would be.<BR>1. Mob/Player filtering (hide wildings/Blink and group other realm players)<BR>2. Distance category to sort by.<BR>More to come as I use it a little more.<BR>Again thanks for sharing this with us non-programers.<BR>----<BR>Now that I read the rest of the post I think CSV of mob and player info to include level, name, location and class would be a HUGE help. And YES crude and less accurate distance sorting would be fine for me.  <BR>---<P><p>[This message has been edited by fodder (edited 12-17-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Slicer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Distance sorting will be a MAJOR cpu hog, as every time you or a mob moves, it has to recalculate the distance and then resort. <BR>Resorting is very CPU intensive. I might make it a non-updating option though, so it resorts only when you click the list... Hmm. I guess I'll try and see.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">fodder</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The distance filter was something that I used extensively in ShowEQ very usefull in a PvP (or RvR) enviornment. I don't know how it worked with ShowEQ but a huge plus to see who was creeping up on you (or running your way) the element of surprise is a huge advantage.<BR>Anyhow just more greatful ramblings</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sparr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Distance sort IS a cpu hog, but so is any other sort.  You wont lose any extra time sorting by dist than by name.  The real problem with dist is the calculation.  Right now we can take a lesson from ShowEQ on dist calculations.  They used to use sqrt(dx*dx+dy*dy) which is true 2D dist.  When I started profiling SEQ for speed I replaced that with dx+dy which isnt as accurate but is much faster.  They are now moving towards some VERY fast fixed-point sqrt approximation algorithms that would probably be good for us to steal.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Have dead friendlies and enemies highlight with different colors in the list.<BR> <BR>Also, have dead people show up with a black center in the radar, when someone is dead, I'm not too concerned with their level.<P>A red outline instead of cyan for enemies makes them stand out much better.<P>I've implemented these changes in my own version of OE and I can attest to their utility<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not a Warden!</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wanna see the ability for filters, so I can look for mobs or players or both.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kreepin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Can we have a sticky name option like in SEQ?  It sucks finally finding a mob in the list..clicking on it and having it scroll on and off the list and you have to scroll around looking for it again.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Drugis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm sorry if I am posting too off-topic:<P>I have recently had to scrap a few of my pcs to re-OS etc. I have been busy at work and had no time to plan much out. However, I have set up a Solaris 8 box because I need it to do some testing. Is it possible to compile OE on Solaris? In the past I have always used SEQ on RH 6.2. I could set up a RH box, but it would be temporary and I'd hate to have to redo it all once I get the right setup for my Linux box.<P>Any idea? Some coding isn't bad - I am a C++ developer (even tho I am coding in Java these days...) but not a huge Unix buff. I use Unix at work but I started on Windows/DOS pcs and never learned intricacies of Unix systems.<P>Any ideas?<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">MII</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How about being able to also see the class of the players around you as well as level and health.  This would be of great assistance in case you have died and need a cleric but they are on /anon or even for grouping to see what classes are around.<P>Slicer, you are the MAN!  Your program is exceptional and I feel it is only gonna get better!  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SirPsycho</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some of my wishlist are:<P>1 - ring drawn around player for maximum visual range (when another player could see you in game)<BR>2 - shaded ring around mobs showing their agro radius <BR>3 - ability to shade around yourself for your maximum attack radius (So I know if I can hit someone from where I am standing)<BR>4 - Display players class<BR>5 - audible RvR spawn alert (will sound if your radar goes from no enemies on screen to having some on your screen)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">As the daoc decryption library is only distributed in binary form, I can't imagine it working on anything except Linux.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">fodder</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here is hopefully an easyone for you Slicer.<BR>In the name list any chance we can have the text show up in the color of the con of the mob/player?<P>Thanks man you rule<P>*I just noticed sort by distance in the settings MANY thanks Slicer*<p>[This message has been edited by fodder (edited 12-23-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
